# Gcore JavaScript Video Player SDK — Cursor Rules

This is the `@gcorevideo/player` SDK — a TypeScript library for embedding HLS, MPEG-DASH, and MP4 video playback into web applications. Built on Clappr with a plugin-based architecture.

## Project structure

```
packages/
  player/
    src/
      Player.ts           # Main Player class — public API
      types.ts            # All public TypeScript types (PlayerConfig, PlayerEvent, etc.)
      index.ts            # Package entry point
      index.plugins.ts    # All plugin exports
      plugins/            # 20+ plugin implementations
      playback/           # HLS, DASH, HTML5 engines
    docs/api/             # Generated API reference
  utils/                  # @gcorevideo/utils — logging, tracing
docs/
  framework-integration.md  # React, Vue, Next.js, Nuxt, Svelte
  architecture.md
  quick-start.md
  player-config.schema.json  # JSON Schema for PlayerConfig
EXAMPLES.md               # Copy-paste recipes
AI-DEVELOPMENT.md         # AI workflow guide
llms.txt                  # Machine-readable SDK summary
```

## Non-negotiable patterns

### 1. Plugin registration BEFORE player instantiation

```ts
// CORRECT
Player.registerPlugin(MediaControl)
Player.registerPlugin(SourceController)
const player = new Player({ sources: [...] })

// WRONG — plugins registered after have no effect on existing instances
const player = new Player({ sources: [...] })
Player.registerPlugin(MediaControl)
```

### 2. autoPlay always paired with mute

```ts
// CORRECT
new Player({ autoPlay: true, mute: true, sources: [...] })

// WRONG — blocked by browser autoplay policy
new Player({ autoPlay: true, sources: [...] })
```

### 3. Always destroy on cleanup

```ts
// React
useEffect(() => {
  const player = new Player(config)
  player.attachTo(ref.current!)
  return () => player.destroy()
}, [])

// Vue
onUnmounted(() => player.destroy())

// Svelte
onDestroy(() => player.destroy())
```

### 4. CSS must be imported

```ts
import '@gcorevideo/player/dist/index.css'
```

### 5. Container needs real dimensions

```html
<div id="player" style="width: 640px; height: 360px;"></div>
<!-- or -->
<div id="player" style="width: 100%; aspect-ratio: 16/9;"></div>
```

### 6. SSR: browser-only library

In Next.js / Nuxt, never import at module level on the server:
```ts
// Next.js — dynamic import
const VideoPlayer = dynamic(() => import('./VideoPlayer'), { ssr: false })

// Nuxt — use .client.vue suffix
// Svelte/SvelteKit — import inside onMount
```

## Plugin registration is global, not per-instance

`Player.registerPlugin()` is a class-level static call. Call it once at app startup — not inside React components or Vue setup functions.

```ts
// app.ts / main.ts — call once
Player.registerPlugin(MediaControl)
Player.registerPlugin(SourceController)
Player.registerPlugin(QualityLevels)
```

## Available plugins

Import all from `@gcorevideo/player`:

**Playback:** `AudioTracks`, `ClickToPause`, `Clips`, `DvrControls`, `MultiCamera`, `PictureInPicture`, `PlaybackRate`, `Poster`, `QualityLevels`, `SeekTime`, `Share`, `SkipTime`, `SourceController`, `ClosedCaptions`, `Thumbnails`

**UI:** `BigMuteButton`, `BottomGear`, `ContextMenu`, `ErrorScreen`, `Favicon`, `Logo`, `MediaControl`, `SpinnerThreeBounce`, `VolumeFade`

**Analytics:** `ClapprStats`, `CmcdConfig`, `GoogleAnalytics`, `NerdStats`, `Telemetry`

## Player API

```ts
// Lifecycle
player.attachTo(element: HTMLElement): void
player.destroy(): void
player.configure(config: Partial<PlayerConfig>): void
player.load(sources: PlayerMediaSource[]): void

// Playback
player.play(): void
player.pause(): void
player.stop(): void
player.seek(seconds: number): void

// State
player.isPlaying(): boolean
player.isMuted(): boolean
player.getCurrentTime(): number
player.getDuration(): number
player.isDvrEnabled(): boolean

// Audio
player.mute(): void
player.unmute(): void
player.setVolume(volume: number): void  // 0..1

// Events
player.on(event: PlayerEvent, handler): void
player.off(event: PlayerEvent, handler): void
```

## Events

```ts
import { PlayerEvent } from '@gcorevideo/player'

PlayerEvent.Ready        // player ready
PlayerEvent.Play         // started
PlayerEvent.Pause        // paused
PlayerEvent.Ended        // reached end
PlayerEvent.Stop         // stopped
PlayerEvent.Seek         // handler(seconds: number)
PlayerEvent.TimeUpdate   // handler({ current, total }: TimePosition)
PlayerEvent.VolumeUpdate // handler(volume: number)
PlayerEvent.Fullscreen   // handler(isFullscreen: boolean)
PlayerEvent.Resize       // handler({ width, height })
PlayerEvent.Error        // handler(error: PlaybackError)
```

## PlayerConfig key options

```ts
interface PlayerConfig {
  sources: PlayerMediaSource[]      // required — URL strings or { source, mimeType }
  autoPlay?: boolean                // default: false
  mute?: boolean                    // default: false
  loop?: boolean                    // default: false — VOD only
  playbackType?: 'live' | 'vod'     // set only if known; omit to auto-detect
  priorityTransport?: 'dash' | 'hls' // default: 'dash'
  language?: string                 // default: 'en'
  strings?: TranslationSettings     // localization
  debug?: 'all' | 'none' | boolean  // default: 'none'
  poster?: PosterPluginSettings     // { url, showForNoOp, showOnVideoEnd }
  cmcd?: CmcdConfigOptions          // { sessionId, contentId }
  dash?: DashSettings               // passed to dash.js
  // plugin options under their name key: googleAnalytics, logo, playbackRate, etc.
}
```

## Source format

```ts
// Short form — MIME type inferred from extension
sources: ['https://example.com/video.m3u8']

// Full form — explicit MIME type
sources: [
  { source: 'https://example.com/video.mpd', mimeType: 'application/dash+xml' },
  { source: 'https://example.com/video.m3u8', mimeType: 'application/x-mpegurl' },
]
```

## Plugin development pattern

```ts
import { UICorePlugin, Events } from '@clappr/core'

export class MyPlugin extends UICorePlugin {
  name = 'my_plugin'       // used as PlayerConfig key for plugin options
  static type = 'core'     // or 'container' for ContainerPlugin

  bindEvents() {
    this.listenTo(this.core, Events.PLAYER_PLAY, this.onPlay)
  }

  private onPlay() { /* ... */ }
}
```

Rules for plugins:
- Extend `UICorePlugin` (core scope) or `ContainerPlugin` (container scope)
- Use `this.listenTo()` — auto-cleans up on destroy
- Templates: `assets/[plugin-name]/template.ejs`
- Styles: `assets/[plugin-name]/[plugin-name].scss`
- Never reference another plugin directly — use Clappr events
- Plugin options accessed via `this.options.[pluginName]`

## TypeScript rules

- No `any` — use `unknown` with type guards
- Export public types from `types.ts`
- Internal types belong in `internal.types.ts`
- Plugin option interfaces: `[PluginName]PluginSettings` or `[PluginName]Settings`

## What NOT to generate

- Do not modify Clappr core directly
- Do not use jQuery — Clappr uses Zepto (`$`)
- Do not break backward compatibility on public APIs
- Do not add `any` types
- Do not import `@gcorevideo/player` at module level in SSR environments
- Do not register plugins inside React components / Vue setup — register at app level

## Debug logging

```ts
import { Logger, LogTracer, setTracer } from '@gcorevideo/player'
Logger.enable('*')
setTracer(new LogTracer('app-name'))
```

## Testing

- Framework: Vitest + happy-dom
- Mock external deps: `dash.js`, `hls.js`, browser APIs
- Test public API and events — not Clappr internals
- Run: `npm test` (from `packages/player`)
